(a)  An electric utility cooperative association shall transfer all non-escheat patronage refunds to a nonprofit corporation incorporated pursuant to chapter 414D. 	(b)  The nonprofit corporation to which non-escheat patronage refunds are transferred pursuant to subsection (a) shall use the non-escheat patronage refunds to:



	(1)	Fund electric energy assistance programs for low-income persons who reside in the service area of the electric utility cooperative association;
	(2)	Make donations to other nonprofit charitable and community organizations, as authorized by its board of directors;
	(3)	Grant educational scholarships to individuals who reside in the service area of the electric utility cooperative association; or
	(4)	Support other appropriate uses for the benefit of the general membership of the electric utility cooperative association, as may be authorized by its board of directors. [L 2005, c 52, pt of §1]
